  "market_context": "On April 29, 2024, CL1! was in a bearish intraday trend. London session continued higher rather than reversing, forming the daily wick. Price reached into a previous range high, signaling a New York reversal setup rather than a London reversal profile.",
  "key_observation": "London continued higher instead of reversing, forming the daily wick by reaching into a prior range. This confirmed a New York reversal profile. At the NY open, price formed a series of up-closed candles (order block) with failure swings from Asia and London resting above, providing a high-probability short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified that London was continuing higher rather than reversing, ruling out a London reversal profile and confirming a New York reversal profile was forming.",
    "Step 2: Noted that the London rally was forming the wick on the daily chart by reaching into a previous range high, establishing the key resistance level.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 30-minute chart and identified a series of up-closed candles at the NY session high as a Change in State of Delivery / intraday order block.",
    "Step 4: Observed failure swings from the Asia and London sessions resting above the order block, confirming liquidity overhead and a high-probability short setup.",
    "Step 5: Planned a short entry with stop above the order block high (or the swing high), targeting the prior session low for a 2.65R reward.",
    "Step 6: Noted the midnight open level offering support context and watched the 8:30 NY open for a potential opposing run to form a new order block.",
    "Step 7: Observed that at 8:30, price made an opposing run upward, forming a new order block on top of the prior order block — identifying this as a Propulsion Block (order block built on an order block).",
    "Step 8: Confirmed the trade hit the take-profit target and noted the propulsion block formation as additional confluence, with the setup also aligned with the midnight open and 8:30 time levels."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit take-profit target at approximately 2.65R. A propulsion block also formed at the 8:30 NY open, providing a second entry opportunity for continuation lower.",
  "lessons": "When London continues higher instead of reversing, frame the day as a New York reversal. Use the intraday order block formed at the session high — especially when stacked with failure swings and aligned with midnight open and 8:30 — as a propulsion block entry for aggressive bearish continuation.",
